The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Donald Trump and First Lady Melania Trump during a National Day of Prayer event at the White House. The President expressed his support for the people of Venezuela and their struggle for freedom. He also recognized the contributions of Vice President Mike Pence and his wife Karen, as well as several members of his administration. The President highlighted the importance of religious freedom and the role of faith-based organizations in areas such as adoption and addiction recovery. He also spoke about recent attacks on religious communities and emphasized the need to combat anti-Semitism and all forms of persecution and hate. The President shared stories of individuals who have overcome addiction and praised the power of prayer. The event concluded with prayers led by various religious leaders.